            "answer_text": "That is a very difficult task. It helps if you become a world class expert in something first. I believe the easiest route is probably as a humanities professor but even that is not easy. I suggest you find a discipline that you are passionate about and spend most of your waking hours becoming one of the premiere experts on that subject in the world. The question was merged after I answered it. The new question about \u201cgetting into a teaching profession\u201d instead of becoming a full professor at MIT is a much easier task. If you are an MIT grad student you will probably be given the opportunity to be a teaching assistant at MIT. ",
